  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good resources to learn web scraping with Python?",
  "response": "Learning web scraping with Python can be both exciting and rewarding. Here are some great resources to help you get started:\n\n### Online Courses\n1. **Coursera**: \n   - \"Python for Everybody\" by the University of Michigan includes a section on web scraping.\n   - \"Data Science with Python\" specialization often covers web scraping techniques.\n\n2. **Udemy**:\n   - \"Web Scraping with Python: BeautifulSoup, Requests & Selenium\" offers hands-on projects and covers various libraries.\n\n3. **edX**:\n   - Look for courses on data science or Python programming that include web scraping as part of the curriculum.\n\n### Books\n1. **\"Web Scraping with Python: Collecting Data from the Modern Web\" by Ryan Mitchell**: This is a comprehensive guide that covers scraping techniques using BeautifulSoup, Scrapy, and Selenium.\n\n2. **\"Automate the Boring Stuff with Python\" by Al Sweigart**: This book has a chapter dedicated to web scraping, and it's a great resource for beginners.\n\n3. **\"Python Web Scraping\" by Richard Lawson**: This book focuses on practical web scraping techniques using various libraries.\n\n### Documentation & Tutorials\n1. **Beautiful Soup Documentation**: The official documentation provides a solid introduction to using this library for parsing HTML and XML documents.\n   - [Beautiful Soup Documentation](https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/bs4/doc/)\n\n2. **Scrapy Documentation**: Scrapy is a powerful web scraping framework. The documentation includes tutorials and examples.\n   - [Scrapy Documentation](https://docs.scrapy.org/en/latest/)\n\n3. **Requests Documentation**: The Requests library is essential for making HTTP requests in Python.\n   - [Requests Documentation](https://docs.python-requests.org/en/latest/)\n\n4. **Real Python**: Offers a range of tutorials on web scraping with Python, covering various libraries.\n   - [Real Python Web Scraping Tutorials](https://realpython.com/tutorials/web-scraping/)\n\n### YouTube Channels\n1. **Corey Schafer**: He has a great tutorial on web scraping using Beautiful Soup and Requests.\n2. **Tech With Tim**: Offers various Python tutorials, including web scraping projects.\n3. **freeCodeCamp**: They often have extensive tutorial videos, including web scraping topics.\n\n### Practice Projects\n1. **Kaggle**: Participate in competitions or explore datasets that require data collection from websites.\n2. **GitHub**: Search for repositories that focus on web scraping projects for inspiration and code examples.\n\n### Forums and Community\n1. **Stack Overflow**: A great place to ask specific questions and find solutions to common web scraping issues.\n2. **Reddit**: Subreddits like r/learnpython and r/datascience can be helpful for asking questions and sharing resources.\n\n### Considerations\n- **Ethics and Legality**: Make sure to respect the `robots.txt` file of websites and understand the legal implications of web scraping.\n- **Rate Limiting**: When scraping, be mindful of the number of requests you make to prevent overloading servers.\n\nBy utilizing these resources, you'll be well on your way to mastering web scraping with Python!",
